Examine an RScore driven analysis vs. a fold change / paired t-test analysis¶

We have been tasked with transfer of the NB-CPACT UCB Covalant Chemical Proteomics Data from Dan Nomuras's lab to share with Novartis scientists. This would preferbly include identification of all probed sites as well as quantitation of reactive sites associated with compound treatement. One common intermediate data format that UCB provides is the IP2 peptideList.csv file.

This notebook will illustrate our current ability to automate hit finding on pepitdeList.csv isoTOP data.

Data sets: Nimbolide EN6

Definitions:

  • RSCORE - For each feature:

         For all quantitation measurements average the ratio of control / test. If any measurement 
     has missing values in test max out at 1000. If any value is missing in control min to 0.001

  • FOLD_CHANGE - For each feature:

          For each sample replicate sum all abundances and divide control over test. 
      fold_change = average(ratios of all samples)

def get_final_ucb_features(xml_file):
    
    df = pd.read_excel(xml_file, sheet_name='final')
    finalUcbPeptides = df['Peptide']

    ucbPeptide2Feature = dataSet.featureDF.copy()
    ucbPeptide2Feature['UCB_PEPTIDE'] = dataSet.featureDF['sequence'].str.replace(r'\([\d.]+\)', '*')
    final_ucb_features = ucbPeptide2Feature[ucbPeptide2Feature['UCB_PEPTIDE'].isin(finalUcbPeptides)]['FEATURE']
    return final_ucb_features

for data_name in data.keys():
    file_path = data[data_name]['file_path']
    feature_type = data[data_name]['feature_type']
    dataSet = transformer.transform(resource=file_path,
                                    transform_function=peplisttransformer.transform_peptidelist,
                                    featureType=feature_type,
                                    test_quant_channel='HEAVY',
                                    control_quant_channel='LIGHT')
    
    dataSet = contrast.build_contrast_data(dataSet, 
                                           normalize_func=data[data_name]['norm_function'], 
                                           max_rscore=data[data_name]['max_rscore'])
    data[data_name]['dataSet'] = dataSet
    data[data_name]['final_ucb_features'] = get_final_ucb_features(data[data_name]['xml_file'])

sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(10,5)})
sns.set_style("white")
sns.set_context("paper", font_scale=0.8)
#sns.set_context("talk", font_scale=0.8)

def label_point(point, x=None, y=None, ax=None):
    bbox = {'fc': '0.8', 'pad': 0}
    props = {'ha': 'center', 'va': 'center', 'bbox': None}
    label = point['FEATURE'].split(',')[0]
    
    ax.text(point[x]+.04, point[y], label, props, rotation=-35, fontsize=12)
        
def do_barplots(dataSet=None, expected_hits=None, datasetName=None, project_results_dir=None):
    ## Abundance Bar Plot
    hits = dataSet.contrastDF[dataSet.contrastDF['FEATURE'].isin(expected_hits)]
    hits = hits.merge(dataSet.featureDF[['FEATURE', 'GENE']], how='left', left_on='FEATURE', right_on='FEATURE')
    hits = hits.drop_duplicates()
    
    for feature in hits['FEATURE']:
        gene = hits[hits['FEATURE'] == feature]['GENE'].values[0]
        
        plotDF = dataSet.normAbundanceMatrixDF.loc[feature, :].reset_index()
        plotDF['SAMPLE'] = plotDF['PAIR'] + "_" + plotDF['CLASS'] 
        
        

        palette_dir = dict(zip(['control', 'test'], sns.color_palette("hls", 2)))

        ax = sns.barplot(x=feature, y='SAMPLE', data=plotDF, palette=plotDF['CLASS'].map(palette_dir))
        ax.set_title('{} ({})'.format(gene, feature))
        plt.savefig('{}/{}-{}.png'.format(project_results_dir,datasetName, feature))
        plt.figure()

def get_hue(feature, expected_hits=None, hit_features=None, contrastDF=None, show_filtered=False):
    finalUcbFeature = contrastDF[contrastDF['FEATURE'] == feature]['IS_FINAL_UCB_FEATURE'].values[0]
    
    if feature in hit_features.values:
        return 'Hit'
    elif feature in expected_hits:
        return 'Expected hit'
    elif (not finalUcbFeature) & show_filtered:
        return 'UCB FILTER'    
    else:
        return ''
    

def do_scatter(contrastDF, px=None, py=None, datasetName=None, xcut=None, ycut=None, 
               expected_hits=None, show_filtered=False, label_all_hits=False, project_results_dir=None):
    
    pallet = sns.color_palette("hls", 3)   
    legend_loc = 'upper left'
    legend_pos = (-10, 0)

    hue = None
    hits = pd.DataFrame(columns=contrastDF.columns)
    if xcut and ycut:
        hits = contrastDF[((contrastDF[px] > xcut) & (contrastDF[py] > ycut))]
        
    hue = contrastDF['FEATURE'].apply(get_hue, 
                                      expected_hits=expected_hits, 
                                      hit_features=hits['FEATURE'], 
                                      contrastDF=contrastDF, 
                                      show_filtered=show_filtered)
    
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x=px, y=py, data=contrastDF, 
                         hue=hue)
    
    sns.despine()
    
    ## Lable features
    hits = contrastDF[contrastDF['FEATURE'].isin(expected_hits)]

    if label_all_hits:
        exp_hits = contrastDF[(contrastDF[px] >= xcut) & (contrastDF[py] >= ycut)]
        label_features = pd.concat([hits['FEATURE'], exp_hits['FEATURE']])
        hits = contrastDF[contrastDF['FEATURE'].isin(label_features)]
    hits.apply(label_point, axis=1, x=px, y=py, ax=ax)
    

    if xcut and ycut:
        title = '{}\nhits={}>{}, {}>{}\n\n'.format(datasetName, px, xcut, py, ycut)
    else:
        title = '{}'.format(datasetName)
    ax.set_title(title)
    #ax.legend(loc=legend_loc, bbox_to_anchor=(0, 0.9))
    
    showfilter_tag = 'show-ucb-filter' if show_filtered else ''
    plt.savefig('{}/{}-x{}-y{}{}.png'.format(project_results_dir,
                                             datasetName, px, py, showfilter_tag))
    
    plt.figure()

def do_plots(datasetName=None, dataSet=None, expected_hits=['YSNSDVIIYVGCGER_C12'], 
             label_all_hits=False, project_results_dir=None):  
    contrastDF = dataSet.contrastDF
    #do_scatter(contrastDF, px='log2(Fold Change)', py='-log10(p.value)', 
    #           datasetName=datasetName, xcut=1, ycut=3, expected_hits=expected_hits)
    
    
    do_scatter(contrastDF, px='log2(Fold Change)', py='-log10(FDR)', 
           datasetName=datasetName, xcut=1, ycut=1, expected_hits=expected_hits, 
           show_filtered=False, project_results_dir=project_results_dir)
    
    do_scatter(contrastDF, px='log2(Fold Change)', py='-log10(p.value)', 
               datasetName=datasetName, xcut=1, ycut=3, expected_hits=expected_hits, 
               label_all_hits=label_all_hits, project_results_dir=project_results_dir)
    
    do_scatter(contrastDF, px='log2(Fold Change)', py='-log10(FDR)', 
           datasetName=datasetName, xcut=1, ycut=1, expected_hits=expected_hits, 
           show_filtered=True, project_results_dir=project_results_dir)

    do_barplots(dataSet=dataSet, expected_hits=expected_hits, datasetName=datasetName, 
                project_results_dir=project_results_dir)
    
    do_scatter(contrastDF, px='RSCORE_RANK', py='log2(rscore)', 
               datasetName=datasetName, xcut=None, ycut=None, expected_hits=expected_hits, 
               show_filtered=True, project_results_dir=project_results_dir)
    do_scatter(contrastDF, px='log2(rscore)', xcut=4, ycut=1, py='-log10(all_psm_p.FDR)', 
               datasetName=datasetName, expected_hits=expected_hits, 
               show_filtered=True, 
               project_results_dir=project_results_dir)
    
    do_scatter(contrastDF, px='log2(rscore)', xcut=None, ycut=None, py='log2(Fold Change)', 
               datasetName=datasetName, expected_hits=expected_hits, 
               show_filtered=True, project_results_dir=project_results_dir)

for dataset in list(data.keys())[:]:
    dataSet = data[dataset]['dataSet']
    expected_hits = data[dataset]['expected_hits']
    final_ucb_features = data[dataset]['final_ucb_features']
    
    dataSet.contrastDF['IS_FINAL_UCB_FEATURE'] = dataSet.contrastDF['FEATURE'].isin(final_ucb_features)
    dataSet.contrastDF['EXPECTED_HIT'] = dataSet.contrastDF['FEATURE'].isin(expected_hits)

    project_results_dir = '{}{}Basic_isoTOPReplicateAnalysis'.format(results_dir, os.sep, prefix=dataset)
    do_plots(datasetName=dataset, dataSet=dataSet, expected_hits=expected_hits, label_all_hits=True, 
            project_results_dir=project_results_dir)
    
    dataSet.save_data_set(directory='{}'.format(project_results_dir), prefix=dataset)
